        <p style="color:rgba(240,253,250,0.92); font-size:14.5px; max-width:660px; margin:0 0 0.8rem;">
          I'm now working on fintech projects, where broken chronological continuity and subtle data leakage don't
          just hurt accuracy, they produce backtests that lie. It's the natural next step from TSAuditor: applying
          the same auditing rigour to financial time-series, market-data pipelines, and risk and trading analytics.
        </p>
        <p style="color:rgba(240,253,250,0.92); font-size:14.5px; max-width:660px; margin:0;">
          The goal is reliable, reproducible pipelines where every model is trained on data that has been audited
          before it's trusted.
